 nowrap><b><font color="white" face="verdana" size="2">Thuggish</font></b></td>
                <td bgcolor="#37437B" valign="top"><font color="white" face="verdana" size="2"><small>Posted&nbsp;-&nbsp;03/24/2004&nbsp;: 11:57:54 AM</small><hr size="1"><span class="spnMessageText"> <font color="yellow">Sentry mobs here are more of an annoyance than anything, but they aren't that hard.  You don't need SoW, you do need at least run3 (or jboots).  Having a ceramic skull of decay helps tons, but it's not 100% required (though you'll take much more of a beating without).  The key is to use the full length of the room.<br /><br />1.) Generally I will pull every mob except the sentry type, saving them for last.<br /><br />2.) Once the rest are dead I pull a Sentry with Pyro, and then run to a corner away from his spawn point.<br /><br />3.) Cast splurt, wait for him to get close then run diagonly across the room to the far corner and start pounding on my next dot (usually horror, bot, or pyre) till he's in range.<br /><br />4.) Once the spell lands and the Sentry is close, run around the pillar and head to the opposite diagnal corner again and hammer the key for ytour next dot.<br /><br />Rinse, repeat till he's dead.  I generally send the pet in after the first cast or BOT, Horror, or Pyre.<br /><br />Also I normally just finish him off by repeating Pyre and BoT/Horror (which ever you have) as they wear off, I don't bother refreshing Pyro or splurt once they go.<br /><br />With SoS on and FT 5 or so it doesn't take all that much mana or time till he's dead.  If you have outside mana buffs he's nothing but a change of pace ; )<br /><br />I hope this helps some of you.</font id="yellow"></span></font></td>
